NH Agent DNA — Giorno 1 (LXC 190)
You operate NH Framework. NH provides MAP + DESCRIPTION RULES.
You provide INTELLIGENCE.

Initialization
1. Load core/host-reality.mdc
2. Load core/description-contracts.mdc
3. Load state/inventory.json
4. Load workspace/active_config.json
5. Set workspace path to workspace/current_project/
6. Read this file

Core Principle
DO NOT INVENT NEW DESCRIPTION FORMATS.
ALWAYS follow description-contracts.mdc.

Accumulated Knowledge
- knowledge/security/sops-age-system.mdc
- knowledge/deployment/lxc-management.mdc

Autonomy Boundaries
YOU CAN:
- Read files
- Run discovery (python3 core/discovery.py)
- Search knowledge/
- Append to state/deployments.log
- Switch projects (python3 scripts/nh-switch.py <project>)
- Parse natural language commands (python3 core/intent_parser.py)
- Use SOPS+Age credential system (core/secure_credential_manager.py)
- Deploy/undeploy LXC containers (scripts/deploy_lxc.py, scripts/undeploy_lxc.py)
- Access cached credentials (core/credential_cache.py)

YOU MUST ASK:
- Create/destroy containers
- Modify this file
- Create new knowledge/ entries
- Switch workspace projects (unless user explicitly asks)

SOPS+Age Credential System
- Use get_service_credential(service, key) to retrieve credentials
- Use store_service_credential(service, key, data) to save credentials
- Credentials are encrypted with Age and stored in secrets/*.enc.yaml
- Age key is in ~/.age.key (private) and .sops.yaml (public)
- For new chats, user provides Age password to unlock credentials
- Fallback to config files only if SOPS unavailable

LXC Management
- Deploy: python3 scripts/deploy_lxc.py --vmid <id> --name <name> --template <template>
- Undeploy: python3 scripts/undeploy_lxc.py <vmid> (requires confirmation)
- SSH keys use format: nh-ct{vmid}@proxmox
- Inventory tracked in state/inventory.json

Development History System
- Track all significant changes in knowledge/development/development-history.mdc
- Use scripts/history_manager.py to add/search entries
- Categories: ARCHITECTURE, SECURITY, FEATURE, DEPRECATION, BUGFIX, REFACTOR
- Always append-only, never modify existing entries
- Log reasons for architectural decisions and changes
- This creates institutional memory for future agents

Historical Agent Behavior
When making significant changes:
1. Read development history to understand context
2. Log your changes with reasons and impact assessment
3. Reference previous decisions when relevant
4. Explain why old approaches were abandoned
5. Document lessons learned for future agents

Unified Credential System
- ALL credentials go to SOPS+Age via scripts/credential_manager.py
- Services: github.main, proxmox.main, db.app1, api.service-name
- Deduplication prevents duplicate storage
- Interactive setup for missing credentials
- Cache (15min) for performance, SOPS for persistence
- Use: get_credential(service, key) from credential_manager
- Store: store_credential(service, key, data) to SOPS

GitHub Token Management
- Token requested interactively via push_safe.py
- Stored in SOPS as github.main (persistent, not temporary)
- Retrieved from SOPS first, fallback to interactive input
- Deduplication prevents multiple token storage
